 Let's start by gathering necessary resources for production
nature();
goto(nearest('tree'));
harvest((-2, 0), count=5);
goto(nearest('coal'));
harvest((-2, 0), count=5);
goto(nearest('iron_ore'));
harvest((-2, 0
), count=5);
goto(nearest('copper_ore'));
harvest((-2, 0), count=5);
goto(nearest('stone'));
harvest((-2, 0), count=5);
inventory();
Now, let's set up our production line by placing the necessary entities.
place('stone-furnace', 0, (1,1));
place('assembling-machine-1', 0, (1,-1));
I apologize for the mistake. I will place it at a different location.
place('assembling-machine-1', 0, (3, -1));
Now, let's set up the inserters and transport belts to move items between the machines.
place('transport-belt', 0, (2, 0));
I apologize for the mistake. Let me correct the placement of the transport belt.
place('transport-belt', 0, (2, -1));
I apologize for the confusion. Let me place the transport belt at another available location.
place('transport-belt', 0, (1, -1));
Now, let's insert some resources into our production line.
insert('coal', (1, 1), count=10);
insert('copper_ore', (1, 1), count=5);
set_recipe((3, -1), 'copper-cable');
